 {"id":"franken_numpy-z8x","title":"[EPIC] Centralize and harden hard-coded numeric constants across all crates","description":"EPIC: Systematic audit and remediation of hard-coded numeric constants in FrankenNumPy.\n\n## Background\n\nA comprehensive audit of all 9 crates identified 34 significant hard-coded numeric constants in production code (non-test). These fall into four categories:\n\n1. **Algorithm convergence thresholds** — absolute epsilon values (1e-10, 1e-15, 1e-30) used as convergence/singularity tests that don't adapt to problem scale (matrix norm, condition number).\n2. **Iteration limits** — arbitrary loop bounds (30, 50, 60*n², 100*n²) for iterative algorithms without documentation of why those specific values were chosen.\n3. **Security/resource bounds** — MAX_* constants for IO parsing, archive handling, and RNG state. These are already named constants and mostly correct, but some lack documentation.\n4. **Display formatting defaults** — threshold, edgeitems, precision for array printing.\n\nThe audit found ZERO instances of TODO, FIXME, or \"will\"/\"would\" comments indicating unfinished code.\n\n## What Was Already Fixed (in the audit session)\n\n- `1e-300` in complex QR → `f64::MIN_POSITIVE` (3 occurrences in fnp-linalg)\n- Taylor series terms `30` → `MATRIX_FUNC_TAYLOR_TERMS` constant (2 occurrences)\n- Denman-Beavers iterations `50` → `SQRTM_MAX_ITERATIONS` constant\n- Logm scaling iterations `20` → `LOGM_MAX_SCALING_ITERATIONS` constant\n- 5 new named constants added to fnp-linalg top-level\n\n## What Remains\n\nThe remaining work is organized as child beads below, covering:\n- Eigenvalue detection thresholds that should scale with matrix norms\n- Iteration limit coefficients that should be centralized (SVD vs eigen QR)\n- Polynomial and root-finding thresholds that should scale with input\n- Display formatting constants that should match NumPy's defaults exactly\n- Documentation for all security/resource bound constants\n\n## Guiding Principles\n\n- **Parity first**: If NumPy uses a specific hard-coded value, we match it exactly. Don't \"improve\" NumPy's constants.\n- **Scale-adaptive thresholds**: Where NumPy uses relative tolerances (e.g., `rcond * max_singular_value`), we should too.\n- **Named constants over magic numbers**: Even if the value stays the same, a named constant with a doc comment is better than a bare `1e-15`.\n- **No behavioral changes without oracle verification**: Any tolerance change must be validated against the differential test suite.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:03:08.422008700Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T03:10:25.812706885Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T03:10:25.812070851Z","close_reason":"Epic created and partially executed during audit session. Remaining work tracked in child beads.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-zcs","title":"Wire SVD_QR_ITERATION_COEFF and EIGEN_QR_ITERATION_COEFF into actual QR loops","description":"## Problem\n\nThe named constants SVD_QR_ITERATION_COEFF (100) and EIGEN_QR_ITERATION_COEFF (60) were created during the audit but the actual QR iteration loops still use the literal expressions. The constants are defined but not yet referenced by the code.\n\n## What Needs to Happen\n\nSearch for all occurrences of iteration limits in QR loops:\n1. SVD bidiagonal QR: look for `100 * n * n` or similar pattern → replace with `SVD_QR_ITERATION_COEFF * n * n`\n2. tridiag_eig_qr: look for `60 * n * n` pattern → replace with `EIGEN_QR_ITERATION_COEFF * n * n`\n3. Hessenberg QR (for general eigenvalues): look for `60 * n * n` → replace with `EIGEN_QR_ITERATION_COEFF * n * n`\n\nNote: The actual code might not use `* n * n` literally — it might precompute `let max_iters = 60 * n * n;` or use a different expression. Search for any integer literal multiplied by n in the QR iteration context.\n\n## Validation\n\n- All linalg tests must pass\n- No behavioral change (same values, just named)\n- Verify the constants are actually referenced (not dead code)\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n- `crates/fnp-linalg/src/lib.rs` — QR iteration loops in SVD, tridiag eigenvalue, and Hessenberg eigenvalue functions","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:06:40.470187014Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T03:17:26.422880345Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T03:17:26.422382493Z","close_reason":"Done as part of franken_numpy-0p9 — all 3 QR loops now use named constants.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-zcs","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-0p9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:07:02.595855131Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-zcs","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-z8x","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-2